# WORDPRESS APPLICATION ON AWS:

1. Deployed an Ubuntu Webserver: Set up an Ubuntu instance on AWS EC2 to serve as the webserver.
2. Configured Elastic IP: Assigned and configured an Elastic IP to ensure consistent accessibility of the server.
3. Installed Apache: Set up Apache HTTP Server to handle web traffic and serve the WordPress site.
4. Installed PHP: Integrated PHP to enable dynamic content processing.
5. Set Up Database: Installed and configured a database to store WordPress data.
6. Installed WordPress: Successfully installed and configured WordPress, including theme and plugin setup.
